SIMPLE: intercepter
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intercepter
<hw>In`ter*cept"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who, or that which, intercepts.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>A high-speed fighter airplane with
fast-climbing capability, used to intercept enemy airplanes or identify
unknown aircraft and engage them in combat if necessary; also, a missile
which intercepts and destroys incoming missiles or airplanes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interception</ent>⟦br⟧
